assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Nexyz. Group Corporation engages in the electricity retail business in Japan. The company offers electric power service to customers ranging from single-family homes to small shops to corporations. It also offers LED lights, kitchen and HVAC equipment, and other energy-saving products. In, addition it engages in content creation and publishing of electronic magazines in various topics, including fashion, politics, economics, lifestyle, and others; production of digital magazines that communicate the charms of local regions through photos, videos, and texts, as well as print publications for local distribution, PR event planning, and tourist PR; and providing e-commerce support and logistics services, and services to facilitate international e-commerce. Further, it operates and franchises a beauty salon; provides stock market investing support services; offers AIMED, a medical resource app that provides information on medical facilities in Japan, as well as allows to make appointments, use AI to diagnose symptoms, and receive remote diagnosis; and provides 3D hologram projection services. The company was formerly known as Nexyz. Corporation and changed its name to Nexyz. Group Corporation in April 2016. Nexyz. Group Corporation was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Shibuya, Japan.
